canJumpOver(Piece) - Method in class com.rafaelbattesti.jungle.WaterTile
Method to determine whether a Piece can jump over it or not.
A JumpingPiece is allowed to jump over it, as long as there is not a SwimmingPiece on it.
canPieceEnter(Piece) - Method in class com.rafaelbattesti.jungle.DenTile
Method to determine if a piece can enter the Den.
canPieceEnter(Piece) - Method in class com.rafaelbattesti.jungle.TrapTile
Method to set the Trap.
Runs when user clicks on the piece next to the Trap.
A piece willing to enter the Trap tile will set any opponent's piece on the Trap rank to 1.
If the user decides not to take the piece on the trap, next round the rank is resetRank() by the removePiece() method.
canPieceEnter(Piece) - Method in class com.rafaelbattesti.jungle.WaterTile
Method to determine whether a Piece can enter it or not.
A SwimmingPiece is allowed to enter the WaterTile with no restrictions.
canTakePiece(Piece) - Method in class com.rafaelbattesti.jungle.JumpingPiece
Method to validate whether a JumpingPiece can take another Piece.
A JumpingPiece can take any opponent's piece with a lower rank.
canTakePiece(Piece) - Method in class com.rafaelbattesti.jungle.StrongestPiece
Method to validate whether a StrongestPiece can take another Piece.
In this project, StrongestPiece extends StandardJunglePiece and represents the Elephant.
The Elephant can take any opponent's Piece apart from the Rat.
canTakePiece(Piece) - Method in class com.rafaelbattesti.jungle.SwimmingPiece
Method to validate whether a SwimmingPiece can take another Piece.
A SwimmingPiece cannot take any opponent's Piece when leaving the WaterTile.
A SwimmingPiece can take another SwimmingPiece while both are on WaterTile.
canTakePiece(Piece) - Method in class com.rafaelbattesti.jungle.WeakestPiece
Method to validate whether a WeakestPiece can take another Piece.
Depends on the returning value of the superclass method, which determines whether a SwimmingPiece can take a piece or not.
In this project, WeakestPiece extends SwimmingPiece.
